<br>
In the first two months of MT's life, guilds came and went.  The &quot;top&quot; guilds weren't really &quot;top&quot; because they didn't do much, and they merged and died and reformed quickly.  Hamunaptra was formed by Nautilus and Bube, and they basically grabbed a bunch of high levellers.  Another proto-guild was Unity of Blades (name might be incorrect) and Sons of the Immortal.  Sons eventually sorta morphed into Circle of the Unseen I believe.  Iron Legions was also a proto-guild that fell apart, many of it's members went to Hamu, and after a while IL was a de-facto &quot;ally&quot; to Hamunaptra, in that it's few remaining members (Ober, Ekelhaft mainly) raided with Hamu.<br>
<br>
The start of the &quot;uberguild&quot; era is the first Fear raid.  Hamunaptra is who formed it, but to be fair it was more along the lines of an open raid.  We allowed guests to tag along, especially back then because there was a decided lack of high level people.  This is approximately 2 months after MT opened.  No one had tried Fear or Hate or Naggy yet.  Hamu did a horrible 15 hour Fear raid that first day, didn't finish.  Next weekend, we went back and managed to clear Fear and kill CT.  While the majority of the raid was Hamu, there were many guests like Ekelhaft, Ober, Xziled, even the Iggles came to a few of our raids.  The next two weekends we did Hate.  Xziled was unhappy over the direction Hamunaptra was going, and wanted to be in charge, so he formed IV at this time.  After we killed Inny, Xziled and IV stopped coming to our raids, and we started being a bit more exclusive.  Hamu tried doing Naggy around this time, but failed because most of our members were over 52.  <br>
<br>
Fast forward about 2 months, to the end of August.  IV is arguably the number 2 guild on the server, they had just finally killed CT and Inny after about 2 months of recruiting and raiding.  Circle of the Unseen was formed around this time, made up of many former members of Sons, plus a bunch of other people.  (CotU might have formed a bit earlier).  HF and TW are farming Naggy and Vox at this time, they are definately 2nd or 3rd string at this point in the server's life.  Around the beginning of September, two events happened.  One, the officers of Hamunaptra essentially left the guild and reformed under a new name, Relentless Ascention.  It also included the last remaining members of Iron Legions (Ekelhaft, Ober, Smirker), and we put Ekelhaft in charge of the guild. (Sucker!) The reason was that we simply felt Hamunaptra had grown too unweildy, and removing people back then was too difficult cause you didn't have the nifty guild management tool you have now.  Hamu never 'fell apart', because it was a purposeful reformation.  About a week or two later, IV left the server en masse to go to the new server opening up, Thoxule Paells (sp).  Those IV members who didn't go to TP ended up joining CotU or Sinister, which was just now starting to get members.  Xune formed Sinister from the core of some PvP guild from UO, plus he mass recruited anyone he could get. (I am not quite sure about the timing on when Sinister started though).    HF and TW were in the planes by now, but they were mainly farming planar armor and HF/Naggy at this time, and were still considered &quot;second tier&quot;.  After farming Hate/Fear for another few months, and XPing in Kunark, RA started thinking about Sev and Trak and VS.  However, Relentless (the monk) wanted to try VS, so he organized a multi-guild raid on VS, made up of members from CotU, Sinister, some HF and TW, and even some RA members (including myself).  VS went down, and it was a kick in the ass to both RA (proving we weren't top dogs anymore) and to Circle/Sinister (proving RA weren't top dogs anymore).  RA responded with the infamous &quot;VS Gank&quot;.  Of course, by today's standards, this seems silly.  RA went in on Wed and killed VS, when Circle and Sinister had planned a raid on VS the following Saturday.   This started some bad blood between the Sinister-Circle alliance and RA.  About 2-3 weeks later, RA tried to kill Trak, and kept wiping due to the horrible lag.  It turned out we were simply using too many people, and the lag was destroying us.  Lytic took Circle and Sinister and killed Trak, which is probably the closest point any other guild or alliance of guilds has come to matching RA as the uberguild.  RA quickly worked to overcome the falling behind, resulting in some races for Trak and VS. In order to stop an all-out gankfest from occuring, the Trak and VS rotations were formed.  Around February, Sinister started falling apart, not sure why.  Xune left, then the next guild leader left, etc.  Circle absorbed many of these Sinister people, as did HF and TW.  I think Circle had some problem around this time too, because they started having problems too.  RA had free reign for quite a while at this time, with no competition in Velious for quite a while.  Unfortunately, attendence in RA was really starting to slack off as well.  With Circle falling apart, and Sinister pretty much gone, HF was the defacto number two guild on the server.  They were still behind RA, and we didn't bump into each other very much until the summer, when HF started doing Klandicar/Zlandicar for ST keys.  Even so, we didn't race each other very often, and when we did, it wasn't very hostile.  Around the end of the summer, attendence issues in RA were getting quite pronounced, and HF was having major attendence issues as well.  Solthan (who had taken over RA when Ekelhaft resigned in March to focus on graduating) and Daggen decided to merge the guilds together into a new, more cohesive guild, and Fury's Edge was born. (I know, many people don't like the name; hey, it's better than &quot;Shadowlordz&quot;)  Somewhere in here, Circle reformed into Reviction (Rev members might know the timeline better than I), and Triune was somewhere in the background.  Also, Royal Jesters was starting to kill stuff on Asian time.  Around October of that year, while FE was trying to break into NToV, TW made a huge push forward.  They started farming Velious content, Klan and Zlan, etc.  FE was killing NToV and ST, while TW started knocking on the door.  Eventually, TW decided to do NToV themselves, and a kind of unofficial rotation began in NToV.  Nothing set in stone, but we kind of kept out of each others way, generally.  Due to the bad blood between TW and HF, there was a lot of animosity between the FE and TW.  When Luclin came out, FE started pushing into Luclin, giving TW more and more access to velious content.  Eventually, FE stopped going into NToV altogether (nerfing Vulak had something to do with this =) .  FE killed 4th Warder in January 2002, AoW about 2 weeks later, and Tunare a few weeks after that.  TW was, if I recall, mainly farming NToV with the occasional foray at the THO.  FE remained ahead of TW all throughout Luclin, though many times TW was &quot;right behind us&quot;.  Usually the content we were farming was the content they were just starting to try.  Sometime last December, TW started slacking off, and Triune and Reviction took over the next spot (dont' recall exactly when, I just know that one day TW was effectively gone).  Around this time, Flames of Vengence (which was Royal Jesters under a new name) started falling apart as well.<br>
<br>
This is the history of the 'top' end of the server.  Hamunaptra turned into RA turned into FE, and has almost always been the top guild on the server in regards to content (Not trying to brag, just trying to be honest).  Other guilds have just as long and colorful a history, and they are welcome to correct any inaccuracies or incorrect timeframes I have listed. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=74028">Neuro the Strategist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
