<br>
LoV formed in the summer of 2k which makes it one of the oldest guilds on MT. I joined shortly after and have stayed and seen a lot of members come and go. We were not anywhere near the top guilds until recently. <br>
<br>
Some of the real old schoolers besides me was Ylander (first GL), Isorn, Angelia, Buller, Marmel, Inusent (had a rogue named Makker later in HF I think). Sorry if I left some names out, don't wanna make the list to long. Some of those ppl went to HF when they grew in power. Some of the old schoolers are on MM now, I still have contact with them from time to time, people like Fableman and Fixarn. I remember the old days, they were a lot of fun.<br>
<br>
Pandore were the old school big French guild, I think there are people out there who could tell their history better, and retelling that hilarious incident with the cleric epic ganking and the following legendary rants. Aurore formed after them and LoV and Aurore have always chased each other until recently. I can safely say that without that competition none of our guilds would have been where we are today so /hug Aurore <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
