<br>
You guys remember when the Trak rotation was being formed? I remember very distinctly that our goal (meaning HF) was to make sure that this server remained the most civillized server in EQ. Once SiN left, that was made much easier. &gt;)<br>
<br>
Man, those were the days... However, I do recall leaving Sons of the Immortal for reputation reasons. They were getting accused of gaking and such, made me not want to be a part of them, anylonger. Kind of a shame, as that was the last time I'd ever be guilded with Morden and some of my other friends, who ended up in CotU.<br>
<br>
By the way, I have always been a firm believer in roleplaying, and I am always happy to oblige whenever I meet anybody who does so. Remember, you can go to raids and wear nice gear, but still have the heart of a roleplayer. There is no need for animosity between &quot;00b3rs&quot; and &quot;RP'ers&quot;. I do remember all the &quot;RP-Server&quot; talk that was going on in the early days, though. Until FV opened up, and we all see how THAT turned out... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Argond Valiantfist</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Grandmaster Geezer of Morell-Thule</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133460" target="top">Geezer-gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E0E0E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mallo>mallo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MT Legend</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(10/14/03 6:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1921.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The low end of the game</span><hr size=1> A scribe writes;<br>
<br>
Neuro speaks of the high end of the game from the forboding grey tower that is the the home of those on the leading edge of the games content.  The petty concerns of the merely mortal who nip at the heels of the great and the near great, though, I doubt he knows as well.<br>
<br>
My lady and I started on this server the week it went live.  <br>
<br>
Predating all the Roleplaying guilds was Two Chalices.  Both good and evil in one guild at war with itself.  This is Eisabeaus (sp?) first guild; some of the best writing you'll see related to this game came out of Two Chalices.  <br>
<br>
White Star Legion was home to many back when the server first started.  You see their guild tags from time to time even now.<br>
<br>
But White Star Legion was not a good home for the roleplayers as they tried to be &quot;all things to all people.&quot;  Amorris, later winner of the BoTB Warrior competition, went to RA from White Star Legion; he gave me a lot of advice when I was starting out.<br>
<br>
Last I saw White Star Legion was still about as of 6 months ago or so.  <br>
<br>
The Roleplayers in that guild though split off and formed Coeur de Lion, my Lady Luniel and Tzen and Mesaoyatun came up with it and stuck me as leader.  <br>
<br>
Shortly before we formed the Order of the White Hand formed.  Thelisakar was the guild leader there and there was much talk of guild war between our two guilds.  War that was interupted by his needing to leave Norrath for demands elsewhere.  Duels and general bad blood.  <br>
<br>
As well Elven Elite is formed in June I believe.  We lost folks that were going to start CdL with us to EE in fact. <br>
<br>
August of 2000 saw the formation of House T'Vlos led by Cynful T'Vlos and his lady Ravensky.  <br>
<br>
House Rea'Morda led by Rusalka and Yaskel.<br>
<br>
and of course Coven of the Blood Rose who predates CdL.  <br>
<br>
As these guilds formed Two Chalices fell.  <br>
<br>
Citizens of Halas formed as did Elves of Surefall Glade.  Elves soon died as well, Eisabeau's second guild.<br>
<br>
Reapers of Sorrow first come to my attention later on so I'm not sure when they formed.<br>
<br>
Eisabeau goes on to EE and the rest of the RP guilds start to stage &quot;raids&quot; into zones.  Most raids are setup around a story, and there is a lot of dueling going on as the large raid forces move.<br>
<br>
2001 finds the formation of Mark of the Draconians Eisabeau's 3rd guild where she is in a leadership role, and the formation of the Hessians of Morell Thule.  Led by folks who didn't care for some aspects of CdL.<br>
<br>
As well most of these guilds are starting to lose their higher levels to RA, HF, HoH, Reviction and Triune.  Folks that have a strong interest in seeing the harder zones and or gaining new gear.  Velious is a strong lure for this.  Armor from ToV, spells, and just the allure of seeing Sleepers Tomb or NToV.<br>
<br>
Add in pressure to get on the VS rotation, you can't complete the Wizard epic if your not on the VS rotation.<br>
<br>
None of the guilds named above could field the force needed for VS in those days.  CdL had the enchanters for it, but not the Tanks or Healers for it.  EE and the Evil Houses could muster the DPS but not the Enchanters.<br>
<br>
The way of the world then was if you were in a small Roleplaying guild you would have to leave.  At about 50th level you left and joined a &quot;real guild&quot;<br>
<br>
The various guild leaders from those guilds talked it over and Gathering of Banners was formed.  The base for Gathering of Banners rose in part from the formation of the Morell-Thule roleplaying council, an OOC group of guildleaders and officers set up to deal with roleplayers' disputes.  In part it came from from the open raids I'd run all through the end of 2001 and most of 2002.  Raids driven by the Ragefire rotation, for then Nagafen had to be dead.  Clerics in Reviction, FE, or Triune would ask their friends in &quot;small guilds&quot; to kill Nagafen quickly to get Ragefire to spawn.  <br>
<br>
All the RP guilds that raided with me, all the unguilded folks that raided with us formed Gathering of Banners.  We've had our arguments; faction in Velious strained and broke friendships.<br>
<br>
Hessians and the Order didn't like some aspects of GoB and pulled out.  The old Citizens of Halas now Civis Macto joined, as did Random Acts.<br>
<br>
And here we sit knocking on the Elemental Planes.  Zones we of course will never see.<br>
<br>
On Rotations:<br>
<br>
Part of what drove GoB into being was the VS rotation.  We had Wizards -- they wanted epics.  We could lose them or we could band together to get on the Rotation list.  <br>
<br>
The Rotations were formed to keep things civil between RA and Sin / CoTU.<br>
<br>
As an up and coming guild I remember discussing with Pandore and with Cereberial back in the day the need to keep the Rotations going.  Even to the point of moderating the VS and Trak rotation when Cads got completely fed up with it.<br>
<br>
The rotations became contentious as the content became more and more trivial to the upper end of the servers guilds but they were still important to the guilds coming up.  It was worth it though because it really did make for a much more civil raiding environment.  <br>
<br>
Frankly something that largely exists to this day.  Are there times when things turn ugly.  Yes, but are they as frequent as on other servers?  I don't think so. I know that Ragefire never got as ugly here as it did on other servers. <br>
<br>
On guildwar:<br>
<br>
Someone mentioned they thought Coeur de Lion and the Order of the White Hand had a guild war.  No, didn't happen and that was for a variety of reasons.<br>
<br>
CdL did fight a war with House T'Vlos in their heyday and lost, and later we fought a war with the Reapers of Sorrow in Neriak 3rd Gate.  That was interesting, when the Rogue guildleader agro'd it did get ugly though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most of the guildwars on this server invloved Mark of the Draconians: they fought the Order of the White Hand, House Rea'Morda.  As well The Hessians of Morell Thule fought in at least one guildwar that I can think of but I forget who.<br>
<br>
Most of my time on this server has been spent with guilds that have chosen to hamstring themselves in one form or another.  Either by limiting the classes you can play (CdL no necros no SKs) or my limiting what race you can be (Reapers can only be Dark Elves).  <br>
<br>
Is it the harder way to play the game?  I don't know; we do all right.<br>
<br>
Mallo Artanos <br>
Guildleader Coeur de Lion<br>
Butcher of the Karanas<br>
<br>
As an aside I mention the mad lady of High Hold Keep a lot in this but no conversation about the Roleplaying guilds on this server can do justice with out mentioning her and her role in the rise and fall of many roleplaying guilds.<br>
<br>
 <p><br>
