<br>
Triune was formed as an &quot;offshoot&quot; guild from Sphere of Legends. SoL's high level players were not satisfied being &quot;bottom feeders&quot; on other high level guild's raids. The original guild leader was not me (although I'm one of the two founding members left). Braonan was the original Triune guild leader.<br>
<br>
We spent our formative months playing around the planes (I still remember our first Fear raid with Enlightened Dawn... that was a debacle if I ever saw one). We focused mainly on getting epics for our members, exploring Velious, and generally just screwing around. We weren't really interested in &quot;uberness&quot; but were mostly interested in being self sufficient enough to host our own raids without relying on other guilds. After a few months, Braonan and his wife Kyri took a break, leaving us leaderless. Since apparently, I'm a masochist at heart, I took over (this story gets more interesting, but since I don't have the energy to write the novel, I'm sure Solwene will enlighten you all if he ever reads this).<br>
<br>
Reviction formed shortly after we did and although we didn't approach the kind of vitriole that the FE/TW spats had, we were still very competitve with each other and continue to be so today. Although now I think we compete to see who can gank RZ from AV first. =)<br>
<br>
Much much drama later, we were able to work through the Velious, Luclin, and now I suppose we could be considered one of the &quot;uber&quot; guilds on the server, although we never really thought ourselves as such. We're still mostly a bunch of friends trying to have a good time; have fun kicking ass as we like to say.  <p><center>
