<br>
Damned good times... and it ain't over yet. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~malaehi_mt/MALSIG.JPG" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39384">What the Gnome wishes he had...</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E0E0E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ennyaorcsbane>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(10/15/03 1:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1921.topic&index=38>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Memories</span><hr size=1> This is an attempt to fill in a few gaps in Mallo's story and provide more detail into one part of the GoBs member guilds. Some of this is from memory of hearsay only so if someone can make corrections, please do. I have been vague in a few places, and even a little &quot;careful&quot; with wording to avoid digging up old rivalries. well, here goes:<br>
<br>
The twilight of the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mark of Draconian</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> happened because of the handling of series of Role-Play events between Eisabeau and Ravinsky (or Rusalka?). The insueing infighting both In Character and Out of Character was devistating, and quickly lead to the shattering of the guild. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Faveo Sulum Ipsemet Ascio</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->* lead by Aaldari,  and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tears of Veeshan</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lead by Solarianne** formed as a result of what happened. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Champions of the Light</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->*** grew substantially as a result of the break-up and the rest of the membership joined other RP guilds or scattered to the wind.<br>
<br>
At the time of the break up, Faveo and Tears were both asked to remain in the GoB, but Faveo decided to go their own way, while Tears decided to stay. (Champions was already a member I believe, if not, they were made a defacto member near this point.) The interesting part about the Tears is that it was founded based on the existance of the GoB. No need for any specific class or raid capability because that was what the GoB provided. <br>
<br>
Tears began as an RP guild with no affiliation besides the general belief that Dragons are generally evil and must be stopped. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.webhazard.net" target="top">www.webhazard.net</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> has more detail, although much of the site is now out of date. As the guild grew in numbers, a new fissure began to form. Those opposed to the way Tears fit into the GoB and what it stands for, and those who liked it. Eventually this fissure snapped and approximately 1/3 of the guild left and formed a new guild, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Protectors of Kindred Souls</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->****.<br>
<br>
Through time, thre were 3 more major events in the history of The Tears. The first was when a group of regular players all joined en masse. I forget the name they used (The Nexus?), but I believe the unofficial leader was a wizard named Astenar. (Urda help me out here.) These were some of the kindest folks I've ever met. They were a regular gaming group (about 10 of them) who liked what they saw of the Tears and decided to join.<br>
<br>
The second being the merging of the Champions of the Light with the Tears. This was a mixed bag. It filled the ranks of the Tears with with Role Players and a few missing classes, but it also pushed together Casual Roleplayers and Hardcore roleplayers. It wasn't long before some of the more hardcore RPers became unhappy with how the guild was going and some left to reform the Champs, and others went to other RP guilds.<br>
<br>
The last major event was when Solarianne, Myself, and Moline left for Triune. This in itself would not be so significant as officers and leaders do leave guilds. The problem was the fact that the resulting events nearly killed the guild as most of the level 60+ members left for Triune, Reviction, Discordians, PoKS, and some ultimately to FE. That in turn caused a number of the remaining members to scatter to guilds all over Morel-Thule including GoB members. Thankfully there were a few very dedicated members who wouldn't let go.<br>
<br>
Because of the efforts of those few dedicated members, Tears of Veeshan is still alive and well under the leadership of Ralstaan and I'm sure, he, or Salvia can explain the more current history. <br>
<br>
If I think of more interesting factoids I'll try to post them. Honestly, this is bocoming very interesting and I think it would be really cool if someone were to try and merge all these stories together to make a history of the guilds on MT.<br>
<br>
I happen to have a Gig or more of logs saved up from my *cough* days of playing on MT that might yield some interesting results. or the most part, I turned logging on 2 years ago and never turned it off. <br>
=============================================================<br>
<br>
* I leave the story about Faveo to be told by Aaldari, but I recommend translating the name from it's latin to get the general idea. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
** It was a common misconception that I was the leader of Tears of Veeshan. This was probably due to my being involved in many aspects of the GoB as well as generally making an ass of myself publicly.<br>
<br>
*** Champions of the Light, if memory serves, was actually originally created as a perminent guild war idea. The Champs and an evil guild would be perminently in a guild war and RPers could join anytime they wanted. As far as I know, there were no real Mains in CotL untill after the MoD breakup. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Aseop</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> would certainly know more about this, but I havn't seen him in a very long time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
**** PoKS was founded by Danadur and any information about it should be asked of him or whoever the leadership is now. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=445727" target="top">Arcanist, Slayer of Dragons</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.webhazard.net/images/ennya/ennya1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
